SOLVER of an ELASTICITY PROBLEM:

1: OBJECT NAME to treat:
   First, the NAME of the object must be given.
   This object has to be meshed and interpolated.

2: ELASTICITY INPUT DATA: 
   The data input for the elasticity problem are:
  -The MASS density, the YOUNG ELASTICITY tensor and the internal
   forces have to be given at level of each material:
   volume in 3D, surface in 2D
  -The IMPOSED DISPLACEMENT (DIRICHLET condition) named here
   FIXATION, the boundary FORCES named FORCE (NEUMANN condition)
   have to be given on every component of the boundary.

   Remark: @ permits the abandon of the data input of a component
           of the object.

   EXAMPLE :
                         L3
       P4 *----------------------------------* P3
          |                                  |
          |                                  |    
          |                                  |
          |                                  |
          |                                  |
       L4 |              S                   | L2
          |                                  |
          |                                  |
          |                                  |
          |                                  |    
          |                                  |
          |                                  |
       P1 *----------------------------------* P2
                         L1

          
   ELASTICITY CHARACTERISTICS for the STEADY problem:

   on S  : ELASTICITY TENSOR and eventually INTERNAL FORCES
   * means one of the 4 characters 1 or 2 or 3 or 4
   on L* : FIXATION (imposed displacement) or
           exterior FORCEs on the boundary L*
   on P* : FIXATION if the point P* is also on one L* which
           supports exterior FORCES

   if L4 and L2 are subjected to exterior FORCES and FIXATIONS for L3
   it is necessary to define P3 and P4 in terms of FIXATION
   in order to imposed a DIRICHLET condition at these points.

   REMEMBER that at least a FIXATION at 3 points not on a same 
   straigth line IS NECESSARY to obtain a PROBLEM INVERSIBLE MATRIX!

   If the object OB is defined by : 
   surface S  line L2  line L3  line L4  point P3  point P4 
   then, by default, the exterior forces on L1 are imposed null.

3: SOLVER of the LINEAR STEADY ELASTICITY PROBLEM
   The data are given. The solver can be executed.
   Choose between a direct method by Cholesky factorization
   or an iterative method by a preconditioned conjugate gradient.

4: DYNAMIC ELASTICITY solver d2/dt2:
   SOLVER of the LINEAR UNSTEADY ELASTICITY PROBLEM
   The data are given. The solver can be executed.
   The TIME INTEGRATION is done with a NEWMARK scheme which is
   unconditionnaly stable.

6: EIGENVALUE & VECTORS solver
   The smaller eigenvalues for the elasticity operator
   may be computed by 2 methods: SUB-SPACE or INVERSE ITERATIONS.

8: DRAWING of DISPLACEMENT & STRESS
   After the displacement computations, the amplified deformed object
   and with arrows the main stresses may be drawn.

10: DRAWING of PLSVO meshes
    To memorize the different meshes and recover the components
    of an object.

The other options are used to manage the project:

20: PRECISION to INVERSE A x = b
    to give the value of convergence iteration test for 
    Cholesky factorization or conjugate gradient.

39: BACKGROUND COLOR of the WINDOW
To change the color of the Mefisto window

71: TOOLS on TMS
With this option, it is possible to
- DISPLAY a TMS (Tableau Memoire Secondaire = Array on Disk)
- INPUT the values of a TMS
- DISPLAY the VALUE of a TMS variable
- IMPOSE  the VALUE of a TMS variable
- CHANGE  a NAME in a directory

72: TOOLS on FILES of the MS
To add a new file to the MS if it is saturated...

73: TOOLS on I/O units
The option 3 (default value) permits the interaction User-Mefisto

74: DELETE TMS of PLSVO
It is possible to DESTROY a  TMS ou un PLSVO or the function 
TAILLE_IDEALE(x,y,z) ... But no recovering is possible!
Don not use this option.

99: SAVE DATA and QUIT
This option is OBLIGATORY to recover the computed TMS of this
execution during a future execution of MAILLER, THERMICER, ...
ELSE, ALL DATA ARE LOST!...

In this wrong case, see the files FRAPPE.* of the project
which permits to compute again all executions...
But, it is not recommended!...
